## English Version

Educational License – CentroWeg – Systems Development Course
Class MIDS 77 - Internet of Things (IoT) Curricular Unit

Copyright (c) 2024 Carlos Eduardo Braga

This software and hardware were developed exclusively for educational purposes as part of the Systems Development course at CentroWeg, Class MIDS 77, during the Internet of Things (IoT) curricular unit, under the guidance of professor Kristian Erdmann and with contributions and assistance from other teachers.

## Granted Permissions

- Anyone may view, copy, or fork this code and circuits for personal or educational purposes.
- It is allowed to study, learn from, and use it as a reference for personal IoT development.
- Running the code as provided in this repository is permitted.
- Reproduction of circuits for educational purposes is permitted.
- Use of libraries and components mentioned in the projects is permitted.

## Restrictions

- Direct modification of this code and redistribution as the original is not allowed.
- Changes may only be made in personal copies or forks, provided the reference to the original code and author is preserved.
- Commercial use is prohibited without the express permission of the author.
- Use of projects for malicious purposes or that may cause damage is not permitted.
- Circuits must be reproduced responsibly and following safety practices.

## Safety Warnings

- Projects contain electronic components that must be handled with care.
- Always test circuits before connecting to the microcontroller.
- Use components appropriate for the specified voltages and currents.
- Work in a safe and well-lit environment.
- For IoT connectivity projects, use secure networks and protect sensitive data.

## Disclaimer

The software and hardware are provided "as is", without warranty of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.

In no event shall the author, teachers, or the institution be liable for any claim, damages, or other liability arising from, out of, or in connection with the software and hardware or their use, including physical, electrical, or any other nature of damages.

## Attributions

This project uses third-party libraries and components that maintain their own licenses:
- Arduino IDE and Arduino libraries
- ESP32 libraries (WiFi, PubSubClient, etc.)
- Electronic components from various manufacturers
- Simulation platforms (Tinkercad, Wokwi)